				<h2>Welcome!</h2>
<p>
This website provides information on events of potential interest to the scientific community 
working on Highly Frustrated Magnetism, both experimental and theoretical, in all of its manifestations 
-- some 200-300 scientists covering all continents.
</p>
<p>
The initiative was borne out of a conference series that started at the turn of the new millennium in 
Waterloo, Canada, and it has now become an established bi-annual event that gathers a large part of the 
community working in this field. 
<!-- HFM 2012 (Hamilton, Canada), HFM 2010 (Baltimore, USA), HFM 2008 (Braunschweig, Germany), 
HFM 2006 (Osaka, Japan), HFM 2003 (Grenoble, France) and HFM 2000 (Waterloo, Canada).-->
</p>

